In Roman times, when a fellow tried
to bribe a public official,

394
00:43:02,630 --> 00:43:04,840
they would cut off his nose,
sew him in a bag

395
00:43:05,050 --> 00:43:08,680
with a wild animal,
and throw that bag in the river.

396
00:43:08,890 --> 00:43:13,270
You tell your master
that we must agree to...disagree!

397
00:43:14,730 --> 00:43:17,940
- You're making a mistake.
- I'm beginning to enjoy my mistakes.

398
00:43:18,150 --> 00:43:22,740
You fellows are 'untouchable'
is that it? No one can get to you?

399
00:43:22,940 --> 00:43:26,320
You tell Capone...
that I'll see him in hell.

400
00:43:29,530 --> 00:43:31,540
Hey! Nice house!

401
00:43:31,750 --> 00:43:34,580
I said, nice house!
Do you live there?

402
00:43:36,250 --> 00:43:39,880
Little girl's havin' a birthday, huh?

403
00:43:40,090 --> 00:43:42,050
Yes.

404
00:43:42,260 --> 00:43:44,510
Nice to have a family.

405
00:43:47,220 --> 00:43:49,930
Yes, it is.

406
00:43:50,140 --> 00:43:54,640
A man should take care,
see that nothin' happens to them.

407
00:44:09,620 --> 00:44:11,580
Catherine?!

408
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:14,960
Catherine!

409
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:17,620
- Where's the baby?
- She's upstairs. Eliot!

410
00:44:30,470 --> 00:44:34,180
- What were you doing up?
- I had to finish my ironing.

411
00:44:34,390 --> 00:44:39,440
You did? You're gonna come
with Daddy now, okay?

412
00:44:51,200 --> 00:44:53,620
Eliot? Okay, it's all right!

413
00:44:53,830 --> 00:44:56,120
Okay, let's go.

414
00:44:56,330 --> 00:45:00,130
Stay there!
Keep your eye on the street!

415
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:05,420
- Where's Malone?
- On the stake-out. He'll be here.

416
00:45:05,630 --> 00:45:09,010
- Who's this guy?
- He's on Malone's list. He's okay.

417
00:45:10,470 --> 00:45:15,020
Drive to the station. She'll let you
know where to go when you get there.

418
00:45:15,220 --> 00:45:17,480
Take off your hat.

419
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:21,020
Anything happens, shoot first.
You understand me?

420
00:45:21,230 --> 00:45:23,440
Yes, Mr Ness.

421
00:45:26,740 --> 00:45:28,400
Kiss.

422
00:45:28,610 --> 00:45:31,740
- Eskimo and butterfly, Dad.
- Okay.

423
00:45:35,290 --> 00:45:37,330
Now, go!

424
00:45:59,390 --> 00:46:01,060
Malone!

425
00:46:02,150 --> 00:46:03,610
- Are they okay?
- Yeah.

426
00:46:03,810 --> 00:46:07,190
- You sure the cop's okay?
- He'd better be, he's my cousin.

427
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:10,610
I want to hurt the man, Malone!
You hear me?!

428
00:46:10,820 --> 00:46:13,780
I want to take the battle to him.
I want to hurt Capone.

429
00:46:13,990 --> 00:46:17,490
Well, then, a Merry Christmas,
we've got some great news.

430
00:46:17,700 --> 00:46:20,160
A huge international
shipment's coming.

431
00:46:20,370 --> 00:46:24,960
We've got the time, the place
and the whole shebang.

432
00:46:25,170 --> 00:46:28,260
Well, what are we doin'
standin' here, then?

433
00:46:29,340 --> 00:46:31,340
How do you come by this information?

434
00:46:31,550 --> 00:46:33,680
That's the second rule
of police work:

435
00:46:33,890 --> 00:46:36,640
if you want to keep a secret,
don't tell the boss.

436
00:46:42,350 --> 00:46:45,190
You know he's making
over $3 million a year?

437
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:47,980
But he's paid no taxes,
nothing's in his name.

438
00:46:48,190 --> 00:46:50,440
If we can establish
any payments to him,

439
00:46:50,650 --> 00:46:53,700
we can prosecute him
for income tax evasion.

440
00:46:53,910 --> 00:46:55,240
What?

441
00:46:55,450 --> 00:46:59,790
I said, we can prosecute him
for income tax evasion!

442
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:03,330
Try a murderer
for not paying his taxes?!

443
00:47:03,540 --> 00:47:06,590
Well, it's better than nothing.

444
00:47:06,790 --> 00:47:10,800
All right. How do we
link him to the money?

445
00:47:11,880 --> 00:47:13,930
I don't know.

446
00:47:15,550 --> 00:47:18,050
Go to sleep, Oscar.

447
00:48:04,770 --> 00:48:07,980
A convoy of 5-10 trucks
with good Canadian whiskey

448
00:48:08,190 --> 00:48:11,860
will be met by a high-level member
of the Capone organisation.

449
00:48:12,070 --> 00:48:15,650
He will be bringing full payment
for the shipment in cash.

450
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:21,740
Now, the meet is to take place just
over the border on the American side.

451
00:48:21,950 --> 00:48:25,160
We want to confiscate
the liquor and the cash.

452
00:48:25,370 --> 00:48:29,290
- Captain?
- We will await their signal.

453
00:48:29,500 --> 00:48:32,630
When they're on the road
and have given the signal,

454
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:36,630
we will engage from
the Canadian side of the bridge.

455
00:48:36,840 --> 00:48:38,840
